CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: " 'Veep' Responds - Vice President Richard M. Nixon responds to a thunderous ovation as he reached the speaker's platform at Syria Mosque last Friday afternoon. The crowd heard Mr. Nixon inform local Republican leaders that the average worker earns more per week and year under the Eisenhower Administration, than even under Franklin D. Roosevelt or Harry S. Truman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Vice President Richard Milhous Nixon speaking at podium, with Arthur T. McGonigle wearing stripped necktie on right, and Hugh Scott wearing vertically stripped necktie and eyeglasses on far right, in Syria Mosque for 1958 Republican campaign
